data.description: Panoramic valley views! Down a long driveway and completely hidden from the road, this fabulous, turn-key property features an exceptionally well-built home in an unparalleled setting. While only 10 minutes to the village of Windham and minutes to Durham, you may never want to leave home! An expansive great room is the heart of this home with a gorgeous stone fireplace and views from every single seat.  The well-equipped, open-galley kitchen features beautiful wood cabinetry, loads of storage and plenty of counter space. The separate, formal dining room is ready for special occasions or when you need more seating. Pine-clad ceilings throughout enhance the warm, rustic ambiance. The large primary bedroom features a roomy en suite bathroom with granite vanity and closets, closets, closets! Two additional, generous bedrooms and another full bath along with a laundry room and half bath complete the first floor. In the walk-out basement, any night is movie night in your own sound-proofed, surround-sound home theater. The cozy family room features a wood burning stove and french doors that open to the garden and fire pit. A reverse-osmosis system has been installed for crystal-clear and clean drinking water and the home has a generator hook-up installed. R19 and R21 insulation keep the entire home warmer in winter and cooler in the summer. Outside, this home features a charming front porch, an Epay hardwood deck off the great room and a two-car attached garage for all your gear. French drains and diverted gutters keep water away from the foundation. The grounds are a nature-lover's delight with two firepits, mature plantings, gently rolling lawn and meadows, woods, stone walls, fruit trees, grape vines and an 8' deep stocked bass pond. The historic barn and paddock in the front of the property lend charm, storage, and room for barnyard friends. Words may not quite be enough - this unique property must be seen to be fully appreciated!
